+- **DW3-CR5 — `IsValidFieldPath` doesn't reject leading `.`, control characters, or `[]`** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore/Controllers/AdminStreamQueryController.cs:IsValidFieldPath]. Beyond DW3's narrow guard scope; ledger lists "empty/whitespace path" as supported. Tracked for future hardening.
+- **DW3-CR6 — Trace-map `producedEvents` list grows unbounded up to MaxEventScan when `expectedEventCount` is null** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore/Controllers/AdminTraceQueryController.cs:142-156`]. Pre-existing scan loop; DW3 only flipped `ScanCapped`. Response-size cap is separate work.
+- **DW3-CR7 — `[AllowAnonymous]` runtime defense (D6 from code review)** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore/Controllers/AdminStreamQueryController.cs:30-32`, `src/Hexalith.EventStore/Controllers/AdminTraceQueryController.cs`]. AC #9 explicitly forbids public-auth changes in DW3. The trust-boundary is documented as accepted-debt; no runtime guard (DAPR-source middleware, IsLocal check) enforces internal-only access. Re-open with a service-to-service auth story when CommandApi exposure changes or when threat-modeling demands enforcement beyond network/DAPR isolation.
+
+## Deferred from: code review of post-epic-deferred-dw5-admin-ui-runtime-follow-ups (2026-05-05)
+
+- **DW5-CR1 — Storage-key substring match for `"compact"`** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/Layout/MainLayout.razor:83`] — `storageKey.Contains("compact", StringComparison.Ordinal)` is fragile if a future tier name embeds the substring. Pre-existing tier vocabulary is fixed; defensive only.
+- **DW5-CR2 — Viewport-tier crossing during keypress writes to wrong tier's key** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/Layout/MainLayout.razor:113-122`] — User resizes between OnAfterRender and Ctrl+B, toggle persists under the new tier's key, prior-tier state untouched. Real edge case but no in-scope user demand.
+- **DW5-CR3 — Holding Ctrl+B (key-repeat) interleaves multiple `InvokeAsync` callbacks** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/Layout/MainLayout.razor:113-122`] — Two awaits inside the InvokeAsync body yield the dispatcher between toggles; visible/persisted state can drift under sustained key-repeat. No throttle/debounce.
+- **DW5-CR4 — Refresh during in-flight Ctrl+B loses the toggle** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/Layout/MainLayout.razor:113-122`] — F5 between `_sidebarCollapsed` flip and `setLocalStorage` resolution loses the change.
+- **DW5-CR5 — Multi-tab same origin: localStorage shared but per-tab `_sidebarCollapsed` field is independent** — Pre-existing; no `storage` event listener.
+- **DW5-CR6 — `focusCommandPaletteSearch` partial-hydration risk** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/Components/CommandPalette.razor:131-135`, `src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/wwwroot/js/interop.js:110-117`] — JS query may run before FluentDialog hydrates slotted children; null `searchElement` silently fails with no retry.
+- **DW5-CR7 — `localStorage` quota exhaustion silently swallowed in JS** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/wwwroot/js/interop.js:48-54`] — Private/incognito browsing or full storage means toggle persists in memory but not across refresh, no telemetry.
+- **DW5-CR8 — Document-level `keydown` listener never explicitly removed on hard navigation** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/wwwroot/js/interop.js:25`] — Relies on browser document-replace cleanup; if `DisposeAsync` throws before unregister, the handler leaks.
+- **DW5-CR9 — `getLocalStorage` returns `null` for both "key absent" and "exception caught"** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/wwwroot/js/interop.js:40-46`] — Caller cannot distinguish; private-browsing user at compact viewport gets default-collapse on every refresh.
+- **DW5-CR10 — `CommandPalette.CloseAsync` no-ops when stale `_isOpen=false` while dialog is visually open** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/Components/CommandPalette.razor:101-122`] — No force-close counterpart to the new force-open. Same stale-state class as the bug worked around for open.
+- **DW5-CR11 — `OnCommandPaletteShortcut` swallows nothing when `_commandPalette` ref is null** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/Layout/MainLayout.razor:101-110`] — Initial-hydration timing window between MainLayout first render and `<CommandPalette @ref>` assignment; user perceives Ctrl+K as broken.
+- **DW5-CR12 — Repeated Ctrl+K spam during Open transition piles up SignalR queue invocations** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/Components/CommandPalette.razor`] — `_isTransitioning` blocks server-side; JS-side has no debounce, latest invocation wins.
+- **DW5-CR13 — Dialog accessibility regex requires `<FluentDialog>` directly followed by `<FluentDialogBody>` with whitespace** [`tests/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI.Tests/Components/Dw5DialogAccessibilityAtddTests.cs`] — Header-slot or conditional template refactors break the regex while preserving the actual aria-label.
+- **DW5-CR14 — `48px` magic CSS pixel value asserted in test** [`tests/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI.Tests/Layout/Dw5SidebarShortcutAtddTests.cs`] — CSS-variable refactor would silently break the assertion even when runtime behavior is correct.
+- **DW5-CR15 — Fluent v5 invariants `Typo|Typography` regex may match `data-typo-test=` attributes** [`tests/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI.Tests/Components/Dw5FluentV5InvariantsAtddTests.cs`] — Defensive false-positive risk on unrelated data-* attributes.
+- **DW5-CR16 — E2E console-error listener does not catch `pageerror`/`websocket close` events** [`tests/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI.E2E/Dw5SidebarShortcutBrowserAtddTests.cs:34-39`] — A subtler renderer-context warning would slip through; only `msg.Type == "error"` console messages are observed.
+- **DW5-CR17 — Evidence narrative claims "3-second bound per click"** — Underlying assertions are `WaitForAssertion(timeout: 3s)` (timeout, not elapsed-time). Narrative slightly overstates assertion strength.
+- **DW5-CR18 — E2E `Console += (_, msg)` event subscription happens after page creation** [`tests/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI.E2E/Dw5SidebarShortcutBrowserAtddTests.cs:33-39`, `Dw5TypeCatalogNavigationBrowserAtddTests.cs:56-62`] — Console messages emitted between page creation and the subscription line are missed.
+- **DW5-CR19 — `OnToggleSidebarShortcut` reads viewport width on every keypress** [`src/Hexalith.EventStore.Admin.UI/Layout/MainLayout.razor:113-122`] — Extra JS round-trip per shortcut; no caching of `getViewportWidth`.
+- **DW5-CR20 — Contradictory dispositions on Ctrl+K reopen** [`_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/deferred-work.md`] — 21-13 entry says "validated end-to-end" but DW5 adds a force-recovery path. Each addresses a different scenario (clean reopen vs stale `_isOpen`); add a clarifying note differentiating them.
